      • apptDeleteMod

        public static boolean apptDeleteMod​(java.lang.String title,
                                    java.lang.String type,
                                    java.lang.String typeObject,
                                    java.lang.String addtlInfo)
        Lambda is used here. This creates a new selection popup window. It allows the user to approve or deny something, returning a boolean value in the process. Lambdas are used in the button trigger methods to make it cleaner as to what is going on and to compress the button action into a clear interface
        Parameters:
        title - The title of the box
        type - Delete vs. modify
        typeObject - the type of object in question (Customer or appointment)
        addtlInfo - any other info to pass to the box for the customer to see
        Returns:
        if the user selects yes, then boolean return is true, otherwise boolean is false.

      • showBox

        public static boolean showBox​(java.lang.String title,
                              java.lang.String type,
                              java.lang.String typeObject,
                              java.lang.String objectName)
        Lambdas are used here. This method shows a popup for the user to select whether or not they want the action performed. Lambdas are used in the button trigger methods to make it cleaner as to what is going on and to compress the button action into a clear interface
        Parameters:
        title - Title is the title of the box set by the window it is called from
        type - Type is either add or remove depending on the window it is called from
        objectName - This is the name of the object (either Appointment or customer) the user wishes to remove/delete
        typeObject - This is the type of the object (either Appointment or customer) the user wishes to remove/delete
        Returns:
        This returns T or F depending on if the user wants to delete or not.
